    "creation_date" : 1391167080,
    "answer_id" : 21478795,
    "question_id" : 5107187,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>suppose your JAR file is in C:\\Documents and Settings\\mmeher\\Desktop\\jar and the JAR file name is xx.jar, then write the below two commands in command prompt:</p>\n\n<p>1> cd C:\\Documents and Settings\\mmeher\\Desktop\\jar </p>\n\n<p>2> jar xf xx.jar</p>\n"
